body:

Credit: Marvel Studios

Avengers: Endgame is a little over a month from its official release. We’re simultaneously ready and not ready for it.

Someone we like is definitely going to die from the original line-up, and we aren’t ready for it. The trailer released last week only served to get us hit in the feelings.

While fans are loving Captain Marvel, we need time to prepare ourselves for what’s to…

summary: Endgame Writer Says Thor Has Tons Of Guilt For Failing To Go For The Head
title: Endgame Writer Says Thor Has Tons Of Guilt For Failing To Go For The Head
excerpt: Avengers: Endgame co-writer Stephen McFeely has said that Thor has a lot of guilt for his infamous blunder in Avengers: Infinity War.
description:
I don’t like it when Thor is sad. It feels wrong.

I mean it’s not his fault that NO ONE TOLD him Thanos was in Wakanda for like twenty minutes of screen time. He could have saved Vision. Why did no one flag him down then?

Where’s Korg? I think he needs to talk to Korg. Korg understands about his hammer.
